00:07:59,562 --> 00:08:02,857
Look how gorgeous these are.

78
00:08:02,857 --> 00:08:05,126
Hong is too skinny for a mermaid dress.

79
00:08:05,126 --> 00:08:07,128
Maybe a princess line dress would suit her better.

80
00:08:07,128 --> 00:08:09,589
An off the shoulder one wouldn't be bad, either.

81
00:08:09,589 --> 00:08:12,650
I should go and pick one for her.

82
00:08:12,650 --> 00:08:15,511
You know it's not your wedding, right?

83
00:08:15,511 --> 00:08:17,847
I would if I could.

84
00:08:17,847 --> 00:08:20,091
I'm all for it, Mom.

85
00:08:20,091 --> 00:08:21,935
All of your hysteria?

86
00:08:21,935 --> 00:08:24,746
It all stems from lack of affection.

87
00:08:24,746 --> 00:08:26,881
Let's get you a boyfriend first.

88
00:08:26,881 --> 00:08:28,232
Speak for yourself.

89
00:08:28,232 --> 00:08:30,826
Scoot over, will you?

90
00:08:36,466 --> 00:08:38,743
- I'm home.
 - Hey.

91
00:08:38,743 --> 00:08:40,686
Are you...

92
00:08:55,900 --> 00:08:58,537
Why do you look so tired?

93
00:09:03,501 --> 00:09:06,880
Oppa Min Jun called and told me that you weren't answering.

94
00:09:06,880 --> 00:09:08,648
Is something going on?

95
00:09:08,648 --> 00:09:12,193
No, I'm just tired.

96
00:09:12,193 --> 00:09:14,328
Let me change first.

97
00:09:15,196 --> 00:09:17,073
Here.

98
00:09:17,073 --> 00:09:21,077
- What's this for?
 - Dad asked me to read it, so I did,

99
00:09:21,077 --> 00:09:24,254
and the story sounded similar to the story of someone I know.

100
00:09:25,050 --> 00:09:29,085
I could be wrong, though. Read it. It's pretty good.

101
00:09:29,085 --> 00:09:31,111
Good night.

102
00:09:38,344 --> 00:09:41,855
 What Comes After Love 

103
00:09:46,878 --> 00:09:50,138
- See you soon. 
 - Thank you.

104
00:09:50,982 --> 00:09:59,317
   
I wanted to ask him... Why did you let me cry alone?  

105
00:10:01,367 --> 00:10:04,128
  Why didn't you stop me from leaving? 

106
00:10:05,538 --> 00:10:10,042
  You didn't stop me or look for me. 

107
00:10:12,904 --> 00:10:16,865
 So, why did you come here after all this time? 

108
00:10:21,012 --> 00:10:23,210
- Eonni!
 - Hong!

109
00:10:24,671 --> 00:10:27,268
I didn't know you were coming, Min Jun.

110
00:10:27,268 --> 00:10:30,463
- Why do you look so down?
 - What?

111
00:10:30,463 --> 00:10:33,066
Wait. Where's your luggage?

112
00:10:33,066 --> 00:10:35,443
I was in a rush, so...

113
00:10:35,443 --> 00:10:37,219
I see.

114
00:10:40,958 --> 00:10:43,276
Welcome back.

115
00:10:47,172 --> 00:10:49,941
I thought you were busy with the exam these days.

116
00:10:49,941 --> 00:10:53,903
Oh, come on. I thought you'd be so happy to see me.

117
00:10:53,903 --> 00:10:55,530
Of course, I'm happy.

118
00:10:55,530 --> 00:10:58,074
Let's quickly go see Dad at the hospital first.

119
00:10:58,074 --> 00:10:59,908
At the hospital?

120
00:11:05,431 --> 00:11:08,300
 Patient Name: Choi 

121
00:11:17,244 --> 00:11:18,511
Dad!

122
00:11:18,511 --> 00:11:20,855
There's my little girl.

123
00:11:22,432 --> 00:11:25,518
- Are you all right?
 - Of course, I am.

124
00:11:25,518 --> 00:11:28,063
- It's not that serious.
 - Why are you back?

125
00:11:28,063 --> 00:11:31,024
You acted as though you'd never come back.

126
00:11:31,024 --> 00:11:32,509
Still, you should have told me.

127
00:11:32,509 --> 00:11:36,613
- Did you say anything when you left?
 - Come on. Don't start.

128
00:11:36,613 --> 00:11:39,749
- It's been ages since we saw her.
 - Who is worrying about whom?

129
00:11:39,749 --> 00:11:42,751
Come on, Honey. That's enough.

130
00:11:44,271 --> 00:11:48,065
Welcome home. Did you eat yet?

131
00:11:51,961 --> 00:11:53,672
Hong.

132
00:11:53,672 --> 00:11:55,131
Coffee.

133
00:11:55,131 --> 00:11:56,665
Thanks.

134
00:12:02,722 --> 00:12:05,125
Is my dad really going to be all right?

135
00:12:05,125 --> 00:12:07,544
Thankfully, he got over the crisis.

136
00:12:07,544 --> 00:12:11,006
Now he'll get better after some more treatment.

137
00:12:11,006 --> 00:12:12,890
Thank you.

138
00:12:13,758 --> 00:12:15,511
Rok told me everything.

139
00:12:15,511 --> 00:12:19,681
I heard you dealt with everything when he collapsed.

140
00:12:19,681 --> 00:12:22,082
I should have been there for him.

141
00:12:23,076 --> 00:12:24,719
Don't say that.

142
00:12:24,719 --> 00:12:28,982
When my parents went to the States, your parents took such good care of me.

143
00:12:28,982 --> 00:12:30,734
It's the least I could do.

144
00:12:30,734 --> 00:12:34,520
Even still. Thanks for everything.

145
00:12:39,051 --> 00:12:40,952
Hong.

146
00:12:40,952 --> 00:12:42,609
Yes?

147
00:12:43,304 --> 00:12:46,958
Did something happen when you were in Japan?

148
00:12:46,958 --> 00:12:48,592
What?

149
00:12:51,396 --> 00:12:54,006
Just a second.

150
00:12:54,006 --> 00:12:56,668
Sorry. They want me in the ER.

151
00:12:57,569 --> 00:12:59,804
You must be tired too.   Hurry  home and get some rest.

152
00:12:59,804 --> 00:13:01,514
I'll call you.

153
00:13:01,514 --> 00:13:03,149
Okay.

154
00:13:16,321 --> 00:13:19,924
Sign here and here as well.

155
00:13:19,924 --> 00:13:23,536
As you instructed, I applied for a loan using the publishing building as collateral,

156
00:13:23,536 --> 00:13:27,140
but they said we'll have to wait to see if it passes appraisal.

157
00:13:27,140 --> 00:13:29,709
I'm putting you through a lot of trouble, aren't I?

158
00:13:29,709 --> 00:13:32,212
Yes. A whole bunch.

159
00:13:32,212 --> 00:13:36,549
- So you'd better get well soon.
 - Fine. I will.

160
00:13:36,549 --> 00:13:39,218
What are those manuscripts over there, anyway?

161
00:13:39,218 --> 00:13:42,480
- Writer Han sent in some more of his work.
 - Another one?

162
00:13:42,480 --> 00:13:46,717
All the employees left, so I'm proofreading this one, too.

163
00:14:14,354 --> 00:14:17,707
You must be starving. How have you still not eaten?

164
00:14:17,707 --> 00:14:19,817
The fridge was completely empty.

165
00:14:19,817 --> 00:14:23,345
- Let's just eat.
 - Thank you for the meal.

166
00:14:38,786 --> 00:14:41,156
 What Comes After Love 

167
00:14:41,156 --> 00:14:44,541
 I assured myself then. 

168
00:14:46,161 --> 00:14:48,870
 That it was all over. 

169
00:14:48,870 --> 00:14:53,582
 That what happened... was just a passing moment. 

170
00:14:55,954 --> 00:15:00,607
 But the two of us were both trying desperately. 

171
00:15:01,918 --> 00:15:08,244
 He was trying to cross my path... and I was trying to avoid him. 

172
