00:15:29,012 --> 00:15:32,507
- Hello. You're early.
 - No, I just got here.

174
00:15:32,507 --> 00:15:35,084
- I'm so sorry about yesterday.
 - Don't be.

175
00:15:35,084 --> 00:15:39,164
Department Head Choi was there to help us, so it went well.

176
00:15:39,164 --> 00:15:40,273
Right.

177
00:15:40,273 --> 00:15:42,483
This is Ms. Miyazawa Hiroko.

178
00:15:42,483 --> 00:15:47,280
She'll be working as your interpreter from now on.

179
00:15:47,280 --> 00:15:51,075
Hello, Mr. Sasae. It's a pleasure to meet you.

180
00:15:51,075 --> 00:15:54,204
It's a pleasure to meet you, too.

181
00:15:54,204 --> 00:15:58,872
I found it interesting that you included a poem by Yun Dong Ju in your recent work.

182
00:15:58,872 --> 00:16:03,930
Is there a favorite line or poem that was written by the poet?

183
00:16:03,930 --> 00:16:09,275
"I found it interesting that you included a poem by Yun Dong Ju in your recent work.

184
00:16:09,275 --> 00:16:14,172
Is there a favorite line or poem that was written by the poet?"

