262
00:21:46,805 --> 00:21:48,517
It's great to finally meet you in person.

263
00:21:48,517 --> 00:21:51,619
Likewise, Ms. Kobayashi.

264
00:21:51,619 --> 00:21:54,639
I heard that you've been taking great care of Mr. Sasae.

265
00:21:54,639 --> 00:21:55,957
Thank you for your assistance.

266
00:21:55,957 --> 00:21:59,777
I should be the one thanking him.

267
00:21:59,777 --> 00:22:03,131
He is a very special person to me,

268
00:22:03,131 --> 00:22:06,408
so please take good care of him.

269
00:22:10,947 --> 00:22:14,566
This should be better than something thick, right?

270
00:22:16,144 --> 00:22:17,678
What?

271
00:22:19,664 --> 00:22:21,198
Right.

272
00:22:23,067 --> 00:22:25,403
Let's go with this one, then.

273
00:22:25,403 --> 00:22:28,681
All right. And what about your tie? Did you have anything in mind?

274
00:22:28,681 --> 00:22:32,135
I think you'd look better in a bow tie than a standard one. What do you think?

275
00:22:32,135 --> 00:22:34,503
Which one should I go with?

276
00:22:37,332 --> 00:22:39,374
- Hey.
 - What?

277
00:22:41,336 --> 00:22:42,920
Right.

278
00:22:42,920 --> 00:22:45,857
- I think they're both nice.
 - Me too.

279
00:22:45,857 --> 00:22:49,819
It's hard to pick something when he looks good in anything, right?

280
00:22:49,819 --> 00:22:53,463
Why do you have to be so good-looking?

281
00:22:54,741 --> 00:22:56,309
Let's go with the bow tie, then.

282
00:22:56,309 --> 00:22:59,938
Do you want to try the second shirt on again?

283
00:22:59,938 --> 00:23:02,789
- Sure.
 - Great. This way, please.

284
00:23:10,031 --> 00:23:13,993
What's going on?
 You know this is your wedding, right?

285
00:23:13,993 --> 00:23:17,830
Just tell them if you don't like the suit.

286
00:23:17,830 --> 00:23:21,000
- It's not that.
 - What is it then? Is it Min Jun?

287
00:23:21,000 --> 00:23:22,226
Hey!

288
00:23:22,226 --> 00:23:25,063
How could you say something like that, all of a sudden?

289
00:23:25,063 --> 00:23:26,965
What?

290
00:23:26,965 --> 00:23:30,234
Why are you so angry?

291
00:23:30,234 --> 00:23:31,511
Honestly!

292
00:23:31,511 --> 00:23:34,938
Are you ready to try on the dresses?

293
00:23:38,309 --> 00:23:42,254
What's taking you so long? Don't you like it?

294
00:23:42,254 --> 00:23:45,151
Can't you at least show us what it looks like?

295
00:23:45,151 --> 00:23:49,173
Do you think she fainted because it looked so good?

296
00:23:49,988 --> 00:23:51,473
Do I have to put a stop to this wedding?

297
00:23:51,473 --> 00:23:53,978
What are you talking about?

298
00:23:53,978 --> 00:23:56,327
It's just the cheesy comments.

299
00:23:56,327 --> 00:24:00,380
I don't know if she can put up with it for the rest of her life.

300
00:24:01,874 --> 00:24:04,918
- Are you jealous?
 - Excuse me?

301
00:24:12,342 --> 00:24:14,618
Could you turn toward the mirror?

302
00:24:15,863 --> 00:24:18,241
Does it feel uncomfortable?

303
00:24:18,241 --> 00:24:20,009
Well...

304
00:24:20,727 --> 00:24:22,704
Is it supposed to feel like this?

305
00:24:22,704 --> 00:24:27,442
It's not exactly your everyday dress. Most people find it awkward at first.

306
00:24:27,442 --> 00:24:29,736
It looks so good, though!

307
00:24:29,736 --> 00:24:33,364
It's not easy to pull this one off, but it looks like it was made for you.

308
00:24:33,364 --> 00:24:36,074
You look absolutely stunning!

309
00:24:36,759 --> 00:24:39,202
I'll wait for you outside.

310
00:24:44,276 --> 00:24:47,795
Remember to give her a big smile, all right?

311
00:24:47,795 --> 00:24:50,731
Oh, of course.

312
00:25:02,544 --> 00:25:04,862
 I'm regretting it. 

313
00:25:05,563 --> 00:25:08,006
For the past five years...

314
00:25:12,387 --> 00:25:15,164
I've never once forgotten about her.

315
00:25:36,928 --> 00:25:39,405
It's so pretty.

316
00:26:28,687 --> 00:26:31,298
It's hard trying on dresses, isn't it?

317
00:26:31,298 --> 00:26:34,569
- You must be exhausted.
 - No. It was fun.

318
00:26:34,569 --> 00:26:36,720
But the dresses weren't my style. That's all.

319
00:26:36,720 --> 00:26:39,568
It's all right. I didn't like this place either.

320
00:26:39,568 --> 00:26:41,284
I'll call a few more places.

321
00:26:41,284 --> 00:26:45,311
Let's call it a day and get something good.

322
00:26:45,311 --> 00:26:49,334
We haven't had tripe in a while. It's your favorite, isn't it?

323
00:26:49,334 --> 00:26:51,527
- Tripe?
 - Oh, right.

324
00:26:51,527 --> 00:26:54,797
We'll just have to go without you since you can't handle it. Sorry about that.

325
00:26:54,797 --> 00:26:58,243
I feel like having a girl's night out tonight.

326
00:26:58,243 --> 00:27:00,119
Is that all right?

327
00:27:01,262 --> 00:27:02,930
Well, sure.

328
00:27:02,930 --> 00:27:05,850
You two can go and enjoy yourselves tonight.

329
00:27:05,850 --> 00:27:06,976
Thank you.

330
00:27:06,976 --> 00:27:10,145
- Let me borrow her just for today.
 - Okay.

331
00:27:10,813 --> 00:27:13,907
- It's all right. Go.
 - Come on.

332
00:27:15,501 --> 00:27:18,003
- See you!
 - See you.

333
00:27:26,603 --> 00:27:28,623
This is so good.

334
00:27:28,623 --> 00:27:32,835
Don't you think the off the shoulder one was much better?

335
00:27:32,835 --> 00:27:36,631
- It was so pretty.
 - But what should I do with my upper arms?

336
00:27:36,631 --> 00:27:38,950
I'm going on a diet starting tomorrow.

337
00:27:38,950 --> 00:27:42,361
What a joke. You're basically just skin and bones.

338
00:27:42,361 --> 00:27:43,721
Hey!

339
00:27:43,721 --> 00:27:45,807
Are you having second thoughts?

340
00:27:45,807 --> 00:27:48,500
- About what?
 - The wedding.

341
00:27:48,500 --> 00:27:50,395
I mean, he's handsome, has a great job,

342
00:27:50,395 --> 00:27:52,397
and was like a son when your dad got sick.

343
00:27:52,397 --> 00:27:54,124
You got yourself a keeper,

344
00:27:54,124 --> 00:27:57,135
but you looked so upset whenever you tried on a new dress.

345
00:27:57,135 --> 00:27:59,328
It felt like I was at a funeral!

346
00:28:00,254 --> 00:28:02,323
Just break it off.

347
00:28:02,323 --> 00:28:03,491
What has he got to lose?

348
00:28:03,491 --> 00:28:07,419
I bet there's a line of girls who would die to marry Min Jun.

349
00:28:10,123 --> 00:28:12,458
What's with the long face?

350
00:28:12,458 --> 00:28:14,584
I feel bad now.

351
00:28:28,266 --> 00:28:30,792
What's with the look?

352
00:28:35,648 --> 00:28:38,133
No, really, Hong, what's wrong with you?

353
00:28:42,329 --> 00:28:44,115
Ji Hui.

354
00:28:44,115 --> 00:28:45,749
What is it?

355
00:28:48,328 --> 00:28:50,395
He's here.

356
00:28:51,414 --> 00:28:53,958
He's in Seoul.

357
00:28:53,958 --> 00:28:57,252
He? Who?

358
00:28:58,004 --> 00:28:59,989
Jungo...

359
00:29:05,700 --> 00:29:09,600
 Tokyo, 5 years ago 

360
00:29:14,145 --> 00:29:16,254
 Jungo was always on the move. 

361
00:29:16,254 --> 00:29:19,108
 I've never seen him just sitting around. 

362
00:29:19,108 --> 00:29:21,552
 Not even once. 

363
00:29:24,948 --> 00:29:26,950
Are you all right?

364
00:29:26,950 --> 00:29:28,984
I'm all right.

365
00:29:34,832 --> 00:29:37,877
 But even when he was busy, 

366
00:29:37,877 --> 00:29:41,581
 I always wanted to be by his side. 

367
00:29:41,581 --> 00:29:44,008
 I wanted to know everything about him 

368
00:29:44,008 --> 00:29:46,177
 and be involved in everything he did. 

369
00:29:46,177 --> 00:29:50,289
 I wanted to be a part of him. 

370
00:29:50,907 --> 00:29:52,934
I made you wait for so long.

371
00:29:52,934 --> 00:29:55,144
You could've gone home without me.

372
00:29:55,144 --> 00:29:56,729
It's fine.

373
00:29:56,729 --> 00:29:58,856
It's been so long since we walked home together.

374
00:29:58,856 --> 00:30:00,650
It's so nice.

375
00:30:00,650 --> 00:30:03,610
- Has it been that long?
 - Yeah.

376
00:30:06,139 --> 00:30:08,574
I'm hungry.

377
00:30:10,159 --> 00:30:13,620
- Shall we stop by the convenience store?
 - Sure!

378
00:30:15,515 --> 00:30:17,249
Let's go.

379
00:30:25,700 --> 00:30:28,385
- Is it good?
 - Yes.

380
00:30:29,053 --> 00:30:31,514
- Beni?
 - Yes?

381
00:30:31,514 --> 00:30:33,573
Can I have a bite?

382
00:30:37,270 --> 00:30:39,704
That's enough!

383
00:30:39,704 --> 00:30:44,874
 Back then, I didn't know what it meant. 

384
00:30:46,078 --> 00:30:50,641
 I simply thought that was normal for people in love. 

385
00:30:54,120 --> 00:30:56,221
Goodbye.

386
00:30:57,582 --> 00:31:00,610
Are you sure you'll be all right without me?

387
00:31:00,610 --> 00:31:04,489
I feel so bad leaving you by yourself.

388
00:31:04,489 --> 00:31:08,034
- Sorry for going without you.
 - Don't be.

389
00:31:08,034 --> 00:31:12,362
People were born to be alone.

390
00:31:12,362 --> 00:31:16,357
Hong. Stop doing that.

391
00:31:16,357 --> 00:31:18,344
Stop pretending to be fine when you're not.

392
00:31:18,344 --> 00:31:21,397
I know that it's tough sometimes.

393
00:31:21,397 --> 00:31:22,857
You can tell me anything.

394
00:31:22,857 --> 00:31:25,902
It's all right to tell me when you're feeling down.

395
00:31:25,902 --> 00:31:27,578
Got it?

396
00:31:28,529 --> 00:31:31,482
I'm actually fine.

397
00:31:32,325 --> 00:31:34,410
There you go again.

398
00:31:34,410 --> 00:31:36,587
Call me when you get to Seoul.

399
00:31:37,914 --> 00:31:40,032
Come here.

400
00:31:44,203 --> 00:31:46,939
Jungo can take care of you now.

401
00:31:48,024 --> 00:31:50,093
Don't cry too much when I'm gone.

402
00:31:50,093 --> 00:31:54,362
- I won't! Just go. Get on the bus.
 - See you!

403
00:32:09,821 --> 00:32:13,866
Jungo. Let's close up and have a drink.

404
00:32:13,866 --> 00:32:17,887
- Oh, no, thanks.
 - There's still time before the first bus.

405
00:32:17,887 --> 00:32:20,223
- I have plans tomorrow.
 - Just stay for once!

406
00:32:20,223 --> 00:32:22,233
Jungo,

407
00:32:22,233 --> 00:32:24,862
it's Nana's birthday today.

408
00:32:24,862 --> 00:32:29,215
I need you to be my wingman, so help me out!

409
00:32:31,217 --> 00:32:33,094
Come and have a drink, Jungo!

410
00:32:33,094 --> 00:32:36,514
- Yes, come on.
 - Take a seat here.

411
00:32:36,514 --> 00:32:38,349
Come on, let's have a drink.

412
00:32:38,349 --> 00:32:40,784
Come on, Jungo!

413
00:33:05,393 --> 00:33:06,794
 Back then, 

414
00:33:06,794 --> 00:33:11,106
 I was very reckless and clumsy. 

415
00:33:20,934 --> 00:33:22,518
So?

416
00:33:22,518 --> 00:33:26,213
- What about the house?
 - We're moving soon.

417
00:33:26,213 --> 00:33:29,876
- Where to?
 - We're moving to Bundang.

418
00:33:29,876 --> 00:33:32,320
Isn't Bundang too far from your school?

419
00:33:32,320 --> 00:33:34,030
 Yes, it's pretty far. 

420
00:33:34,030 --> 00:33:37,074
Three hours there and back.

421
00:33:38,326 --> 00:33:40,536
Whatever.

422
00:33:40,536 --> 00:33:43,714
 I wish I could move out like you. 

423
00:33:44,582 --> 00:33:47,126
What about Dad?

424
00:33:47,126 --> 00:33:49,762
- How's he doing?
  - What do you think? 

425
00:33:49,762 --> 00:33:53,215
His life's work is about to get closed down.

426
00:33:53,215 --> 00:33:56,385
 He's all over the place these days. 

427
00:33:59,430 --> 00:34:02,225
Hey, did you get into graduate school?

428
00:34:02,225 --> 00:34:06,311
- What?
  - Haven't you heard back from them yet? 

429
00:34:07,230 --> 00:34:08,964
No, I have.

430
00:34:10,066 --> 00:34:12,192
I failed.

431
00:34:14,112 --> 00:34:18,908
- You must be so upset.
 - It's probably for the better.

432
00:34:18,908 --> 00:34:21,168
It was too expensive, anyway.

433
00:34:23,554 --> 00:34:28,525
 Doshisha University Letter of Acceptance 

434
00:34:59,360 --> 00:35:01,260
I'm an honest person.

435
00:35:01,260 --> 00:35:03,660
You're such a liar.

436
00:35:12,086 --> 00:35:13,671
Hey, Miss.

437
00:35:13,671 --> 00:35:18,666
You're always running alone. Do you want to have a drink with me?

438
00:35:18,666 --> 00:35:22,395
Hold on! Just stay for one.

439
00:35:23,448 --> 00:35:25,382
Are you all right?

440
00:35:26,225 --> 00:35:29,729
Miss! It's only one drink!

441
00:35:29,729 --> 00:35:32,147
Hey, come back!

442
00:35:43,918 --> 00:35:46,045
Excuse me!

443
00:35:46,045 --> 00:35:48,297
Is everything all right?

444
00:35:51,501 --> 00:35:53,627
Are you all right?

445
00:36:05,974 --> 00:36:08,084
I'm sorry.

446
00:36:08,084 --> 00:36:11,187
Your friend's not answering his phone.

447
00:36:11,187 --> 00:36:13,923
Would you like to wait here a little longer?

448
00:36:13,923 --> 00:36:16,009
I see.

449
00:36:16,009 --> 00:36:17,668
I'm fine now.

450
00:36:17,668 --> 00:36:19,988
Thank you.

451
00:36:19,988 --> 00:36:23,099
- Will you be all right by yourself?
 - Yes.

452
00:36:23,099 --> 00:36:25,250
I'll be fine.

453
00:36:34,627 --> 00:36:37,212
Thank you for everything.

454
00:36:51,327 --> 00:36:53,296
 Ishigami Hospital 

455
00:36:53,296 --> 00:36:57,400
Fortunately, it doesn't look too serious.

456
00:36:57,400 --> 00:37:00,187
It might be tough to go home with crutches.

457
00:37:00,187 --> 00:37:02,381
Do you have anyone to help you?

458
00:37:03,281 --> 00:37:05,574
Just a moment, please.

459
00:37:09,679 --> 00:37:11,305
 Yun Oh 

460
00:37:11,305 --> 00:37:14,083
Good evening, gents. Come on in.

461
00:37:14,083 --> 00:37:16,961
This way, please.

462
00:37:16,961 --> 00:37:18,946
A party of three.

463
00:37:19,510 --> 00:37:21,400
Can you drink more?

464
00:37:21,400 --> 00:37:24,792
 Beni 

465
00:37:31,551 --> 00:37:34,061
Thank you, that's 30,000 yen  (≈ $200) .

466
00:37:38,066 --> 00:37:41,085
Here's your change of 120 yen.

467
00:37:41,085 --> 00:37:47,373
This is your statement, receipt, and medication.

468
00:37:47,373 --> 00:37:51,320
- Have a good night.
 - Thank you very much.

469
00:37:52,905 --> 00:37:54,639
All done.

470
00:37:55,475 --> 00:37:57,243
I'm so sorry.

471
00:37:57,243 --> 00:38:00,313
You're so busy but I troubled you.

472
00:38:00,313 --> 00:38:04,258
Not at all. It's really no trouble at all.

473
00:38:04,258 --> 00:38:08,554
- I'll put your medicine here.
 - Thank you so much for your help.

474
00:38:08,554 --> 00:38:11,765
- Can you manage?
 - I'll be fine.

475
00:38:48,494 --> 00:38:51,029
Did you lose your phone?

476
00:38:52,348 --> 00:38:54,182
No...

477
00:38:57,353 --> 00:39:01,516
- We were completely swamped tonight.
 - I'm sure.

478
00:39:01,516 --> 00:39:05,693
You're always busy with work, Jungo.

479
00:39:05,693 --> 00:39:08,539
I'm always second to everything else.

480
00:39:08,539 --> 00:39:11,192
What are you talking about, Beni?

481
00:39:11,192 --> 00:39:12,635
But it's true.

482
00:39:12,635 --> 00:39:14,938
Do you even know what I'm worried about

483
00:39:14,938 --> 00:39:17,941
or what's going on with me these days?

484
00:39:17,941 --> 00:39:22,651
I'm so sorry about today.

485
00:39:22,651 --> 00:39:24,805
Only today?

486
00:39:27,800 --> 00:39:32,305
If you're really sorry, quit all your jobs.

487
00:39:32,305 --> 00:39:33,973
Come on, Beni.

488
00:39:33,973 --> 00:39:38,311
Work is like a life lesson for aspiring writers like me.

489
00:39:38,311 --> 00:39:39,879
You know that.

490
00:39:39,879 --> 00:39:43,601
On top of that, I need to work to pay for college.

491
00:39:43,601 --> 00:39:45,608
What about me?

492
00:39:47,095 --> 00:39:50,439
What am I to you, Jungo?

493
00:39:51,440 --> 00:39:54,085
Whether I go to the police station or a hospital,

494
00:39:54,085 --> 00:39:56,604
does any of that matter to you?

495
00:39:56,604 --> 00:40:01,526
- That's not what I meant— 
 - Why do I always have to be alone?

496
00:40:01,526 --> 00:40:03,778
How are you alone, Beni?

497
00:40:03,778 --> 00:40:06,197
We go to bed and wake up together every day.

498
00:40:06,197 --> 00:40:08,082
I...

499
00:40:10,910 --> 00:40:13,079
I...

500
00:40:13,079 --> 00:40:14,873
I only work very hard

501
00:40:14,873 --> 00:40:18,877
because I want to be with you.

502
00:40:18,877 --> 00:40:20,837
I can't...

503
00:40:20,837 --> 00:40:22,989
understand

504
00:40:22,989 --> 00:40:26,308
why you're working so hard.

505
00:40:27,719 --> 00:40:30,305
I can't stand the fact that

506
00:40:30,305 --> 00:40:33,308
I have no one else I can vent to.

507
00:40:33,308 --> 00:40:35,943
You're the only one I have.

508
00:40:45,153 --> 00:40:49,290
 Solitude can make a person anxious. 

509
00:40:53,495 --> 00:40:55,388
 Solitude... 

510
00:40:55,388 --> 00:40:58,132
 weakens love. 

511
00:41:00,043 --> 00:41:02,028
 And... 

512
00:41:02,028 --> 00:41:04,789
 when youth is added to the mix, 

513
00:41:05,507 --> 00:41:08,009
 everything... 

514
00:41:08,009 --> 00:41:10,227
 becomes precarious. 

515
00:41:12,430 --> 00:41:15,225
 Seoul, present  
 Hey, just forget it. Forget all about it.

516
00:41:15,225 --> 00:41:17,352
It's all good now.

517
00:41:17,352 --> 00:41:19,229
So, you said to that guy...

518
00:41:19,229 --> 00:41:22,248
You told that good-looking guy what the deal was, right?

519
00:41:22,248 --> 00:41:24,292
You told him you're getting married soon.

520
00:41:24,292 --> 00:41:27,028
Yes. I did.

521
00:41:27,028 --> 00:41:29,520
- I told him straight out.
 - Well done.

522
00:41:29,520 --> 00:41:33,450
- There's no reason for you to see him again, anyway.
 - That's right.

523
00:41:33,450 --> 00:41:36,705
As long as the interpreter shows up,

524
00:41:36,705 --> 00:41:40,083
or unless I run into him on the streets out of the blue,

525
00:41:40,083 --> 00:41:41,830
I won't ever have to see him again.

526
00:41:41,830 --> 00:41:44,020
- Okay! 
 - Okay!

527
00:41:44,026 --> 00:41:46,265
- One more drink!
 - Yes!

528
00:41:46,265 --> 00:41:49,676
I'm down. Excuse me, sir.

529
